RobotServlet, java.io.Serializable, javax.servlet.Servlet, javax.servlet.ServletConfig
public abstract class AbstractRobot
extends javax.servlet.http.HttpServlet
implements RobotServlet

An abstract implementation of a Robot that handles deserialization of events and serialization of operations and implements callbacks for the profile and capabilities.

Author:
douwe@google.com (Douwe Osinga), mprasetya@google.com (Marcel Prasetya)

processEvents

public abstract void processEvents(RobotMessageBundle events)
Description copied from interface: RobotServlet
The main event loop for a Robot. The robot will process the set of events as a whole or one by one. Each event contains the Wavelet, Blips and Documents that are affected. More context and content are provided for an event depending on the settings in the Capabilities XML configuration. Modifications to the Wavelet, Blips and Documents attached to an event will generate operations that are transmitted back to the Wave Robot Proxy and applied to the original Wave as intended.

Specified by:
processEvents in interface RobotServlet
Parameters:
events - The set of events to be processed.
